:QUOTE [subtitle:Harper Lee, quotetype:PLAIN]
You never really understand a person until you consider things from his point of view.

:JOURNEY
Rereading To Kill a Mockingbird
Read
Impact
- Reading at 12 | 5 | Heroism clear | Atticus felt simple and the morality unambiguous
- Reading at 18 | 4 | Cracks appear | The comfort of the narrative begins to fracture
- Reading at 24 | 3 | Framework limits | The white savior structure becomes visible
- Reading now | 4 | Complicated love | A more honest relationship with a flawed book

